gomodel:SYNGO_4753  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: Electron micrographs of asymmetric (excitatory) terminals (A and B) and symmetric (inhibitory) terminals showed AP3-μ3B (AP3M2) knockout mice had reduced amount of SVs and SVs were smaller in diameter. \"Thus, these results indicate that AP-3B is involved in the biogenesis of synaptic vesicles in hippocampus in vivo\"\n\nFigure 4: Impairment of GABA release, but not glutamate, was observed due to reduction of VGAT in AP3-μ3B (AP3M2) knockout mice.. Experimental description: \"we generated mice lacking μ3B, a subunit of AP-3B\"\n\nM&M: \"RT-PCR was performed using sense (5'-atgctggacaatgggttcccc-3') and antisense (5'-aattgtagggttctcatcggg-3') primers for μ3B\".\n\nNucleotide BLAST confirms this is mouse Ap3m2 (i.e. top-hit was XM_030243706)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-04" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4753" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

